                {
                  "$type": "Models.Functions.MultiplyFunction, Models",
                  "Name": "BunchesPerPlant",
                  "Children": [
                    {
                      "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
                      "Text": "\r\nNumbers were guessed based on Eltom 2013 Fig. 6.3. However, this is based on the mean daily temperature from 12 days pre-budbreak. the model only work forward, and can not know the budburst date before it actually happens. Furthermore, for the moment, it always require to calculate from certain phenological stage instead of actual date. \r\n\r\nFlowers per bunch is affected by the temperature and CHO during initiation, which affects the number of primary branches, temperature and CHO during bud burst, which affect the secondary braches and flower initiation, ",
                      "Name": "Memo",
                      "Children": [],
                      "IncludeInDocumentation": true,
                      "Enabled": true,
                      "ReadOnly": false
                    },
                    {
                      "$type": "Models.Functions.Constant, Models",
                      "FixedValue": 300.0,
                      "Units": null,
                      "Name": "meanFlowersPerBunch",
                      "Children": [],
                      "IncludeInDocumentation": true,
                      "Enabled": true,
                      "ReadOnly": false
                    },
