                {
                  "$type": "Models.Functions.MultiplyFunction, Models",
                  "Name": "BerriesPerBunch",
                  "Children": [
                    {
                      "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
                      "Text": "\r\nPercentage of fruit set were guessed based on mean daily temperature during anthesis (Eltom 2013 Fig. 6.5, y = 0.5*x-8 (wrong equation)). temperature range is 15.5 to 16.2 degree. \r\n\r\nThe minimum function was try to cap the maximum berry number and the predicted yield. Due to the size of the peducle or bunch frame, it was not able to sustain lots of berries at harvest even so there was more at fruit set.  ",
                      "Name": "Memo",
                      "Children": [],
                      "IncludeInDocumentation": true,
